			"description": "One-loop s-channel four-point Witten diagram in $AdS_4$ treated as a twisted period integral in parametric (projective) form with five Feynman parameters. Multiple Symanzik-like polynomials $U_1,\\ldots,U_4$ and an $F$ quadratic in cross-ratio variables $(\\zeta_0, \\zeta, \\bar\\zeta)$ are given. Two degree-2 annihilators plus the Euler homogeneity operator generate a D-module of holonomic rank $r=4$ with singular locus $\\zeta\\bar\\zeta(\\zeta-1)(\\bar\\zeta-1)(\\zeta-\\bar\\zeta)$ (affine $\\zeta_0 \\to 1$). A fourth-order Picard-Fuchs operator in $\\zeta$, exact in $d=4-2\\varepsilon$, is derived for the first time and factorizes into four linear factors as $\\varepsilon \\to 0$, consistent with a polylogarithmic solution at leading order. Propagators in momentum space are not given since this is an AdS (position-space) Witten integral.",
